<h1 id="hangup">Hangup</h1>

<p>The hangup command can be used to terminate a call.</p>

<p>Within the hangup command, the following supporting element can be provided:</p>

<ul>
<li>
<em>reason</em> - rejected/busy, default rejected. This value tells BlueVia what to play down the line to the caller. Busy responds with a standard busy time. Rejected will play a standard not in service response</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="json-examples">JSON Examples</h2>

<p>The following examples demonstrate how you can use the hangup command</p>

<ul>
<li>
    <p><em>hangup</em> with a <em>reason</em></p>

    <pre><code>  {"commands": [
          {
              "hangup": {
                  "reason": "busy"
              }
          }
      ]
  }
</code></pre>
  </li>
</ul>
