<h1 id="redirect">Redirect</h1>

<p>The <em>redirect</em> command allows you to specify a URL that will provide subsequent call control functionality. This is typically used within call control command chains. Upon completing a specific call control command you may wish to provide subsequent commands to be performed on the call. This provides a powerful tool to add additional commands to a call based on current call state</p>

<p>Within the redirect element there is only a single parameter:</p>

<ul>
<li>
<em>actionUrl</em> - specifies the URL that you wish to retrieve the next set of commands from.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="json-examples">JSON Examples</h2>

<p>The following examples demonstrate how you can use the redirect command</p>

<ul>
<li>
    <p><em>redirect</em> with a <em>actionUrl</em>:</p>

    <pre><code>  {
      "commands": [
          {
              "speak": {
                  "text": "Let's redirect this call",
                  "voice": "Female"
              }
          },
          {
              "redirect": {
                  "actionUrl":"&lt;your domain&gt;/&lt;your commands&gt;√î√á√ò
              }
          }

      ]
  }
</code></pre>
  </li>
</ul>
