</code></pre>

<p>Then finally you simply format the HTTP POST request and make the request passing in the commands. Simple. couldn‚Äôt be easier right? ;-)</p>

<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> There is also the option of passing in the callback URL into the setcommands HTTP POST request. In this case you would not pass in the commands in the body of the HTTP POST request, but instead a callback URL to a location that specifies the commands. This is discussed further in the <a href="/alpha/restref/calls/">Calls Resource</a>  documentation</p>

<p>So you have seen how to create a call using the BlueVia RESTful API. Have a look at the next quick start guide to see how you can <a href="/alpha/quickstart/restapicreateconf/">create conference calls</a> using the API.</p>

